IBM Watson Advertising (IWA), formerly The Weather Companyâ€™s advertising sales division, uses the worldâ€™s leading artificial intelligence (AI) technology to unlock data and insights and help marketers make better decisions. IWA offers trusted, insight-driven media, data, and technology solutions that can be deployed across a Brand or Platformâ€™s entire marketing strategy to help drive results. 
 
Your Role and Responsibilities 
IBM Watson Advertising is hiring an Ad Trafficker. You will be a member of the Ad Operations Department and reports to an Ad Operations Manager. You will be responsible for partnering with the Client Services Team for trafficking, management, optimization, reporting and quality assurance of all digital ad campaigns. In direct support of Premium, Programmatic, and Local Ad Sales, you will translate client needs into actionable tasks and see them through to completion.
 Support our Sales Team with launch and trafficking functions for advertisersâ€™ online advertising campaigns, utilizing our order management system and ad server. 
Partner with the Campaign Manager and Account Manager in management and optimizations of complex ad campaigns. 
Upload, QA, and assign creative tags and assets for campaign trafficking. This may include late night or after hour support for some of our top strategic accounts and products. 
Provide QA and be a go-to resource for troubleshooting support for ad campaigns, including creating test pages and a focus on creative, delivery, quality, and technical integrations. 
Provide administrative support as necessary in the form of contract review or client reporting. 
Assist with any necessary ad reporting out of the ad server or from partner interfaces in order to validate delivery, identify issues, and provide support to internal teams. 
Provide support to Programmatic initiatives: managing ad server operations for Programmatic Guaranteed Campaigns, troubleshooting Preferred Deals and other Programmatic Campaigns, fulfilling reporting inquiries, setting up new Programmatic Partnerships etc. 
Support the Local Reseller business by ensuring campaigns are set up properly, responding to client questions, and partnering with the Program Management Team in resolving any issues. 
Work on ad hoc interdisciplinary projects to grow skill set and learn different aspects of Digital Ad Operations and Ad Sales. 
Required Technical and Professional Expertise 
 
1.5 years+ of experience managing complex operational processes in online advertising or related industry 
Knowledge of working with third party Ad Ops tools (e.g. Charles, Fiddler, Advalidation, Ad-Juster, and/or similar systems) 
Experience working with an ad server (Google Ad Manager experience preferred) 
Dependable with a positive, solution-oriented attitude 
Preferred Technical and Professional Expertise 
 
Ability to establish and maintain strong relationships within the Sales organization 
Experience working with HTML, VAST/Video and other Rich media formats 
Be a creative thinker and strong project manager. 
Extremely detail-oriented with strong analytics, problem solving, and decision-making skills 
Interest in improving processes and operational efficiency 
